cucumber-expressions: [JavaScript] use Regex extension for group indices

The becke-ch--regex--s0-0-v1--base--pl--lib library augments regular
expressions so it's possible to get indices for capture groups.
This is not possible with JavaScript's standard regular expressions
(https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1985594/how-to-find-indices-of-groups-in-javascript-regular-expressions-match)
and this library handles that nicely.
